# =============================================================================
# canopy/native — .gitignore
# Keep: all source, the gradle wrapper, the vendored header trees + the small,
# NON-reproducible libfbjni.so prebuilt. The LARGE, Maven-reproducible vendored
# .so (Hermes/JSI/onnxruntime — ~63 MB) are NOT committed (CI-5): a fresh clone
# stays < 50 MB and restores them with `scripts/fetch-vendor.sh` (keyed to the
# checksummed host/vendor.lock.json). See docs/vendored-binaries.md.
# NO keystore is committed. The dev keystore (host/android/canopy-release.jks) is
# regenerated/obtained locally — never committed (see docs/ci-secrets.md for the
# keytool one-liner). Production AND CI signing comes from CANOPY_STORE_FILE gradle
# properties materialized from CI secrets (CANOPY_KEYSTORE_BASE64 + passwords),
# never the repo.
# Ignore: every regenerable build artifact, machine-specific config, and secrets.
# =============================================================================

# ---- Canopy compiler output / cache (regenerated by `canopy make` / `canopy-native build`) ----
canopy-stuff/
artifacts.dat
*.elco
package/output/

# ---- JS bundles are build output (integrity-checked, never committed; rebuild with canopy-native build) ----
**/canopy.bundle.js
**/canopy.bundle.js.map
**/canopy.manifest.json

# ---- Generic build dirs ----
**/build/
**/.cxx/
host/shared/build-android/
host/shared/build-host/
# CI bundle staging (scripts/build-app-bundle.sh stages the shippable bundle here; regenerable)
/dist/

# ---- Autolink: generated by `canopy-native` from the dep graph each build (never committed) ----
host/android/app/src/main/jni/generated/
host/android/app/src/main/java/com/canopyhost/generated/
host/android/canopy-autolink.gradle
host/android/canopy-autolink.cmake
host/android/canopy-autolink.AndroidManifest.xml
host/ios/CanopyHostCore/Generated/

# ---- Haskell / Stack ----
**/.stack-work/
*.hi
*.o

# ---- Android / Gradle ----
**/.gradle/
**/local.properties
**/captures/
*.iml

# ---- iOS / Xcode (generated; pods + frameworks are fetched/vendored by remote-build.sh) ----
**/DerivedData/
**/Pods/
host/ios/**/*.xcodeproj/
host/ios/**/*.xcworkspace/
host/ios/Podfile.lock
host/ios/node_modules/
host/ios/Frameworks/*.xcframework/
host/ios/Frameworks/*.framework/

# ---- Remote build harness: secrets (the SSH target / IP lives here) + pulled artifacts ----
**/.remote-build.env
**/.remote.env
**/remote-artifacts/

# ---- Production signing secrets (NO keystore is ever committed; see docs/ci-secrets.md) ----
keystore.properties
*.p12
*.pem
*.jks
release.keystore
host/android/canopy-release.jks

# ---- Vendored .so: fetched, not committed (CI-5 — keeps a fresh clone < 50 MB) ----
# These are reproduced byte-identically from upstream Maven AARs by scripts/fetch-vendor.sh,
# gated on host/vendor.lock.json. Ignored so they can sit in the working tree (for local
# builds) without ever re-entering git history. libfbjni.so is the ONE exception — it is small
# and NOT reproducible from the obvious upstream (hand-stripped, provenance unrecorded — see
# scripts/revendor.sh), so it stays committed (the `!` un-ignores it).
host/android/vendor/lib/*/libhermes.so
host/android/vendor/lib/*/libjsi.so
host/android/vendor/onnxruntime/lib/*/libonnxruntime.so
!host/android/vendor/lib/*/libfbjni.so

# ---- Node ----
node_modules/

# ---- Example local-dev accommodations (regenerated; see examples/counter/README.md) ----
examples/*/external/
examples/*/output/

# ---- Editors / OS ----
.DS_Store
*.swp
.idea/
.vscode/
*.log
